@startuml level-4q-code-backpressure-pattern
!define DIRECTION left to right
skinparam {
    backgroundColor #F5F5F5
    defaultFontSize 11
}
skinparam rectangle {
    BackgroundColor<<producer>> #FFCCBC
    BackgroundColor<<queue>> #BBDEFB
    BackgroundColor<<consumer>> #C8E6C9
    BackgroundColor<<signal>> #FFE082
    BorderColor #E65100
}

title Level 4: Backpressure & Flow Control Pattern (Adaptive Throttling)

rectangle "Producer\n(Fast event source)" as prod <<producer>> {
    rectangle "Proc<State, Msg>\ntell(DataMsg)\nRate: 100K msg/s" as prodProc
}

rectangle "Mailbox\n(Message Buffer)" as mbox <<queue>> {
    rectangle "Bounded queue\nCapacity: 1000 messages\nThreshold 80%: 800 pending" as qData
    rectangle "Queue pressure\n• 0-50%: normal\n• 50-80%: caution\n• 80-100%: backpressure" as qStat
}

rectangle "Consumer\n(Slow processor)" as cons <<consumer>> {
    rectangle "Proc<State, Msg>\nprocess(msg) → 1K msg/s\n(10x slower!)" as consProc
}

rectangle "Backpressure Signal\n(Feedback loop)" as signal <<signal>> {
    rectangle "Monitor: queue size\nTrigger: 80% threshold\nAction: reduce producer rate" as sigLogic
}

prod --> mbox: tell(DataMsg)\nAsynchronous send
mbox --> cons: dequeue(FIFO)\n10 ms per msg

cons --> signal: signal when\nqueue > 800 msgs

signal --> prod: SlowDown(rate=50%)\nTell producer to throttle

note right of prod
  Producer doesn't know
  about queue depth.
  Unaware of consumer speed.
end note

note right of qData
  Bounded mailbox prevents
  unbounded memory growth.

  Without backpressure:
  Producer sends 100K/s
  Consumer processes 1K/s
  → Queue grows 99K/s
  → OOM in ~10s
end note

note right of cons
  Consumer processes at
  natural speed: 1K/s
  No awareness of producer.

  Backpressure effect:
  Producer automatically slows
  to prevent queue overflow.
end note

note right of signal
  Backpressure mechanism:

  Stage 1 (0-50%): Normal
  └─ tell() = instant

  Stage 2 (50-80%): Caution
  └─ tell() may queue slightly

  Stage 3 (80%+): Critical
  └─ Producer receives signal
  └─ Reduces rate to 50%
  └─ Consumer catches up
  └─ Queue drains
  └─ Rate restored
end note

@enduml
